13/07/2008
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Seventeen ethnic Albanians received a total of 192 years in jail sentences on Friday (July 11th) on charges of terrorism.
The 17 included one Albanian national and three Kosovars.
They faced charges of armed attack against the police, preparation of a terrorist act and weapon possession.
Police arrested 13 of them after staging Operation Mountain Storm last November in the village of Brodec.
(Makfax, A1, Kirilica - 11/07/08)
